# {{project_name}} — Claude Code rules

Claude Code-specific enforcement for this repo. General agent guidance
is in `AGENTS.md`. This file only records the rules the tool itself
should honor.

## Absolute rules

- **Do not shell out to `kubectl`, `helm`, or `docker`.** They are
  explicitly disallowed by `.claude/settings.json` (except through
  `python -m harness:*`). If a task seems to need a direct call, you
  are missing a subcommand — ask the user.
- **Writes under `{{workspace_dir}}/**` go through without an approval
  prompt.** The PreToolUse `guard-path` hook enforces that only allowed
  paths are writable, and the PostToolUse `log-tool-call` hook records
  every Write/Edit/Task/kagent call to the session log. You get no
  interactive gate — the logs are the audit trail. Keep edits small and
  intentional so the log stays readable.
- **Never edit** `harness/**`, `.claude/**`, `config/**`, `context/**`,
  `docs/**`. These are denied at the settings layer and by the
  PreToolUse hook.
- **Session logs are authoritative.** When reporting results, link
  `session_log` from the CLI JSON envelope rather than repeating output
  inline.

## Tools you should actually use

| Task | Tool |
|---|---|
| Running a harness subcommand | `Bash(python -m harness <...>)` |
| Full deploy cycle | `/deploy <phase> <service>` (slash command) |
| Diagnosing a cluster issue | `Task(subagent_type="runtime-diagnoser", …)` |
| Reading a phase spec | `Read(context/phases/<phase>.md)` after loading `phase-spec-reader` skill |

## Slash commands

- **`/deploy <phase> <service>`** — run the full verify-apply-verify
  pipeline via `deploy-orchestrator`. The orchestrator validates that
  `context/phases/<phase>.md` contains `## Service: <service>`.
  Everything else (static-only, diagnose-only, scaffold) is a direct
  call from the main session as described in `AGENTS.md`.

## Things not to do

- Do not invent additional slash commands.
- Do not create separate log files; append to `$HARNESS_SESSION_LOG`
  via the CLI only.
- Do not summarize session output by pasting long excerpts. Point to
  the session log file.
- Do not modify `{{workspace_dir}}/tests/**` — smoke tests are
  out-of-band.
